 art history, but also across those of cultural geography, architecture and urban planning, environmental history, and landscape studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aArtxPolitical aspects. 0aCultural landscapes. 0aLand usexPolitical aspects. 0aLandscape architecture. 0aLandscapes in art. 7aART / History / Contemporary (1945-).2bisacsh1 aScott, Emily Eliza, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSwenson, Kirsten J, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311062111208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016z978311065748740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520961319423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520961319.jpg  a978-3-11-062111-2  UC Press eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  a978-3-11-065748-7  UCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles